            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The \"spell\" feature is owned by Vim, so I would suggest you open this issue at vim/vim and see what happens. Whatever approach they implement, we will likely port.\n\nOn the Neovim side, our efforts are better spent in enabling \"spelling plugins\" (maybe via in-process LSP servers?) so you could replace the legacy spellchecker with an existing blocklist checker of your choice.",
